The President held a meeting to discuss the current Ebola cases in the US and receive an update on the actions being taken in response. The investigation into how the healthcare workers in Dallas were exposed to the virus was discussed, as well as the contact tracing process. The President also ordered steps to enhance the CDC's ability to respond to Ebola cases. The need for federal authorities to work closely with state, local, and hospital officials in case of another positive diagnosis was emphasized. The meeting also covered protocols to ensure that lessons learned from the Dallas experience are shared with hospitals, clinics, and healthcare workers nationwide. Participants in the meeting included the Secretary of Health and Human Services, the White House Chief of Staff, the National Security Advisor, the Assistant to the President for Homeland Security and Counterterrorism, and the Director of the CDC.